13. Rxb7 Nc6 {[%mdl 32768]} 
14. Bh6 Qc8! { A nice move, freeing up the d8-square. } 
15. Qb3 Rd8 
16. Rb5 ( { With the d4-bishop defended, we are now threatening } 16.-- Na5 { . } { After the immediate 15...Na5? 16.Qa4! Black suddenly is in serious trouble as 16...Nxb7 will be met by 17.Qxd4 . } ) Bg7 { I like this move, seeking to eliminate White's bishop pair and carving out the d4-square for our knight in the near future.

The position is equal with best play, but I think White has to be much more careful since if we can consolidate our position and maintain a knight on d4 long-term, then White will be left with a bad vs good minor piece dynamic. } 
