This is hard for Black to avoid without taking a lot of risk as the symmetrical structure coupled with the early exchange of minor pieces reduces winning possibilities.

Fortunately, at the non-professional level, this tends to be less of a concern as the higher number of mistakes will create more opportunities in the middlegame and endgame than can be seen by an examination of Grandmaster games. } 
