This game may not show the latest in opening theory or serve as a good illustration of how to respond to some of White's most challenging lines in the modern era. However, in my view, it is a very instructive game as Garry Kasparov embodied the aggressive and dynamic spirit of the Grünfeld and showed just how quickly the White player can land themselves in trouble if they choose a dubious approach to the opening. } 
