14. Rxb7 Nc6 { As this is a repertoire course, we have been focusing on the best moves available to White and Black at every turn. While this is good practice when studying theory, it can also be deceptive as we may be left with the impression that most middlegames that we will reach will be approximately equal positions.

In truth, most opponents will soon deviate from best play, which will give us the opportunity to quickly gain an advantage. In this game, we see the Israeli Grandmaster Ori Kobo making a significant error with his move. This allows Black to quickly seize an advantage. } 
