15. Qa4 { This is the most challenging move. The point is that White not only pressures the knight on c6 but also threatens to bring the f1-rook to the d-file soon. If Black is not precise then he could end up with a lack of piece coordination that results in material losses. } Qc8! { A powerful multi-purpose move. Black defends the knight, steps the queen away from the d-file, and targets White's undefended rook. } 
