This means that White has no way to advance since they cannot mobilize the pawn majority without exposing their king too much (and allowing a perpetual check, at the least).

Now seems like a good time to mention that as Grünfeld players it is especially important to be comfortable with major theoretical endgame positions as it is not rare that we will be required to defend the 'bad side of a draw' from time to time. } ) Rxa7 
